Genetically engineered Marines travel throughout Space, battling depraved heretics, dishonourable traitors, and vile aliens.

This set includes 4 powered gauntlets, two holding the torn off heads of two different types of alien beast - a brutal ork, and a sinister soulstealer. The third holds a retro style space beaky helmet, and the fourth is empty, perhaps for you to add in your own head model! All four have supported versions.

This is an updated version of the first thing I ever tried to 'sculpt', as opposed to arrange geometric shapes - an ork head. It's a little reflection on my part, comparing where I started to where I am. It's been a slow process, as I take what digital hobby time I can in between physical modelling and all my other fickle interests! But it's still nice to see what I feel in some improvement.

You can see the original here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/power-gauntlet-prime-scale-powered-gauntlet-holding-head

I am an amateur enthusiast 3D designer, and appreciate all constructive feedback. Please check out my other designs for more wargame models, and please consider following me, posting a make, or even leaving a donation via my profile!

Leading their brothers into battle, the chaplains of the Prime Marines in Space wear deaths-head helmets to strike fear into their foes.

Inspired by a recent grim-dark computer game, this studded, skull-faced helm would be an interesting conversion piece for your grim dark future wargame models. I'm working on a number of other comparable heads, so hopefully more packs will follow soon! 

Included are supported and unsupported versions of the file, plus a slightly scaled up version with larger studs.

A full set of Skull helmets, with a whole range of additional variations, can be found here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/prime-skull-helmets-set

Commentary :

All of the design backgrounds were based on the Roguetrader (1st Edition) and the 2nd and 3rd Edition designs.

As always, based on the design of the time, I mixed the design sensibilities of the present era.

Personally, I recommend that the size of the shoulder pad is 105-108%, and the size of the head is 95%. (That looks good.)

I got a lot of help from my colleague, LegioXIVguy, in determining the ratio and size. So the overall size is about between New edition Chaos space marines and Primaris marines.

Please enjoy the Retro work.

The Warp, the final final frontier. This is the battleground of the Crusaders. Their eternal mission to explore strange new worlds, seek out foul xenos, to boldly go where no marine has gone before... and then kill them.

Lost Crusaders continue on the incredible mission laid before them by the Emperor of Mankind before he went off to sit upon his porcelain throne never to be seen again. Their mission is endless, their resources strained, and lacking all the fun new toys the later generations get. For this proud few band of brothers failure is not an option, at least not one they are willing to entertain.

Submitted for the approval of the Midnight Society: The Eternal Crusaders
